15/03/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Police have succeeded in collecting nearly 40 per cent of the weapons stolen from army facilities and police precincts during the 1997 turmoil, according to sources cited by the local press Tuesday (15 March).
Police also report that about 15 per cent of stolen munitions and 9.2 per cent of engineering munitions have been collected thus far.
(Albanian News - 15/03/05)
